HEADWORD: Calamanco
<hw>Cal`a*man"co</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧l`⟦adot⟧*m⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧"k⟦osl⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>calamancus</ets>, <ets>calamacus</ets>; cf.
<ets>camelaucum</ets>; a head covering made of camel's hair, NGr.
<grk>kamelay`kion</grk>, and F. <ets>calmande</ets> a woolen
stuff.]</ety> <def>A glossy woolen stuff, plain, striped, or
checked.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A gay <xex>calamanco</xex> waistcoat.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Tatler.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

